parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission valve assembly can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
an unknown yellow warning light is illuminated
the vehicle is unable to accelerate above a certain speed (e.g.
40 mph)
the vehicle must be driven at a slow speed (e.g.
7 mph).

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Output Sensor and Transmission Control Module (TCM) Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the output sensor and TCM can cause the vehicle to fail to accelerate, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to accelerate above a certain speed (e.g.
40 mph)
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vibration caused by the transmission can lead to a loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates when traveling at certain speeds (e.g.
40 mph
65 mph)
significant vibration can be felt in the center console
armrest
steering wheel
and front seats
the vibration is more pronounced when driving uphill in ECO mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission speed sensor can cause the vehicle to suddenly stop accelerating, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle will stop accelerating without warning
then start moving again after an hour
the engine light may not illuminate during the incident
but will later display codes P0500
the vehicle may surge forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause injuries to the driver and passengers, and may lead to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: Airbags deploy without warning
airbags deploy during normal driving conditions
airbags deploy without any prior indication of a malfunction
airbags deploy while turning or cornering
seatbelts become locked after airbag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Intelligent Key Not Detected error can cause the vehicle to decelerate unexpectedly, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents, especially when driving on the highway.
symptoms: The vehicle displays an Intelligent Key Not Detected error message
the accelerator becomes unresponsive
the vehicle decelerates
the warning lights
infotainment center
and A/C remain operational
the vehicle may not start after power down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to continue turning in a full circle, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Abnormal sound while turning the steering wheel
the steering wheel continues to turn in a full circle
no warning lights are illuminated.
